The '''Rote myzomela''' ('''''Myzomela irianawidodoae''''') is a species of Indonesian [[honeyeater]] endemic to the island of [[Rote Island|Rote]]. It is considered distinct from the [[Sumba myzomela]] based on voice. It was named after [[Iriana Joko Widodo]], the first lady of Indonesia at the time of description. It has a scarlet head and nape, as well as lower back and tail, and a dark grey upper back and light grey stomach. It is threatened by habitat loss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.mongabay.com/2018/01/meet-indonesias-new-honeyeater-species-from-rote-island/|title=Meet Indonesia's new honeyeater species from Rote Island|website=news.mongabay.com|author=Basten Gokkon |date=5 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ornithomedia.com/magazine/etudes/description-nouvelle-espece-oiseau-indonesie-myzomele-rote-iriana-widodo-02595.html|title=Description d'une nouvelle espèce d'oiseau en Indonésie, le Myzomèle de Rote (d'Iriana Widodo) {{!}} Ornithomedia.com|website=Ornithomedia|date=January 2018 |language=fr-FR|access-date=2018-01-06}}</ref>

